  "cutList": [],
  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Cut pickets down to size",
      "body": "Cut the pickets to length, then rip them down to three inches on using the table saw.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/646937ce96aa7035.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Scalloped Edge",
      "body": "You can use whatever shape you want for your scalloped edging. We used a two inch radius. Trace them out, cut them on your saw of choice. We used a band saw and finished them using an oscillating belt sander.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/ad12f660f64e4ec6.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Mitered Corners",
      "body": "Take eight of the pickets and miter the corner with a forty-five degree miter. Glue / clamp them and set them of to the side to dry.\n\n**Tip:** Be sure to make a right and left.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/b650a2142c89685d.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Pocket hole the Carcass Stiles and Sides",
      "body": "Pocket hole the carcass, stiles and sides.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/0f3437ac0b224b0f.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Assemble the Carcass Front and Back",
      "body": "Glue and screw the stiles to the top and bottom.\n\n**Tip:** We used a framing square to try and keep things square.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/0e714c568f1b8701.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Assembling the front and back",
      "body": "Using a narrow crown staple gun, attach the corner pickets to the front and back, then add the remaining center pickets.\n\n**Tip:** Hide the pocket holes by having them face the pickets.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/35ef202f63292b1f.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Shelf pin Jig",
      "body": "We wanted to maximize the versatility of these planters, so using a Kreg Shelf Pin Jig we drilled holes into the front and back, allowing for the plants to adjust up and down.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/3cb6f826ccb3f053.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Sides",
      "body": "Attach the carcass sides, then attach remaining center pickets",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/d0b8d47cccae1310.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Leg Bracing",
      "body": "Cut leg bracing on the miter saw.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/70c5da767e6089f1.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Add Legs",
      "body": "Attach the corner bracing to the bottom of the carcass, then screw the leg brackets and legs to the corner bracing.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/6b7d3004ab522e05.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Trim",
      "body": "Add trim of choice. We ripped down a 2x4, and routed the edges using a 5/8\" round over bit. You can get 2 pieces out of the thickness of a 2 x 4.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/fad53f2cad38977e.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "Final assembly",
      "body": "Glue and screw the shelf together, cut the louver light cover to size and assemble.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/1b5e0fdcc4dd2fd1.webp"
    }
  ],
